      "content": "idk. i was just looking at some stuff about the heat death of the universe and it just hit me. everything we do, every single thing... it's all just noise. in a billion years, or even a trillion, there won't even be a memory of us. it feels so stupid to keep trying when the end result is just zero. like, why even bother with the struggle?",
